                <img src="/posts/meshtastic-client-update-1/P_20250829_200306.jpg" referrerpolicy="no-referrer">
            </div><p>My goal with this project is to build a fully open-source <a href="https://meshtastic.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Meshtastic</a>/<a href="https://meshcore.co.uk/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Meshcore</a> compatible client that is more &ldquo;rugged&rdquo; than what is currently available on the market. If there is enough interest, I will consider manufacturing a few and getting CE etc. certification done. If you are interested, please join the mailing list below.</p>]]></description></item><item><title>VBZ's new custom built multi-purpose vehicle</title><link>https://stefan.schueller.net/posts/vbz-multifunctional-vehicle/</link><pubDate>Tue, 17 Jun 2025 20:30:16 +0200</pubDate><author><name>Stefan Schüller</name></author><guid>https://stefan.schueller.net/posts/vbz-multifunctional-vehicle/</guid><description><![CDATA[<div class="featured-image">
